25
00:01:27,879 --> 00:01:29,005
Tell me what you want.

26
00:01:29,589 --> 00:01:32,967
There's a report that came into
the Yeongmoonpo Police Department.

27
00:01:33,051 --> 00:01:34,385
In a parking lot,

28
00:01:34,469 --> 00:01:37,347
a guy on a motorcycle slashed a man's neck
and then got away.

29
00:01:38,014 --> 00:01:39,057
Write this.

30
00:01:39,808 --> 00:01:44,479
Seoul, Gangdong, A 6438.

31
00:01:45,146 --> 00:01:47,649
No need to look it up.
It's a fake license plate.

32
00:01:48,525 --> 00:01:50,527
Find out where
the guy on this motorcycle is hiding.

33
00:01:52,320 --> 00:01:55,365
- Do you know how hard it is--
- I know it takes a long time.

34
00:01:56,032 --> 00:01:57,242
That's why you'll do it.

35
00:01:58,118 --> 00:02:00,453
It's 10:00 right now.
I'll give you five hours.

36
00:02:00,537 --> 00:02:01,830
If you can't find him…

37
00:02:03,456 --> 00:02:06,251
…your cousin's little striptease
will be online.

38
00:02:06,334 --> 00:02:09,045
Try to pull something on me,
and it'll also find its way online.

39
00:02:09,129 --> 00:02:11,965
If you don't want to see
lil Group's stock prices tank,

40
00:02:12,048 --> 00:02:13,258
I suggest you do well.

41
00:02:13,341 --> 00:02:14,175
Good luck.

42
00:02:18,596 --> 00:02:19,430
What is it?

43
00:02:19,514 --> 00:02:21,933
735629.

44
00:02:29,357 --> 00:02:30,233
See you soon.

45
00:02:34,988 --> 00:02:36,156
Fuck you!

46
00:03:07,020 --> 00:03:10,190
BLOODHOUNDS

47
00:03:17,113 --> 00:03:18,072
Hello, sir.

48
00:03:18,156 --> 00:03:20,074
- Whoa, salute!
- Salute!

49
00:03:20,158 --> 00:03:23,328
Soju's on me. I'm buying.

50
00:03:30,585 --> 00:03:32,629
- This way, sir.
- Right, thank you.

51
00:03:32,712 --> 00:03:33,963
- Sir.
- Hello.

52
00:03:37,050 --> 00:03:40,011
They boil the bodies for days
until the bones get soft.

53
00:03:40,094 --> 00:03:42,430
They grind them up
and pour them into the ocean.

54
00:03:42,513 --> 00:03:44,557
It costs 15 million to do all that.

55
00:03:44,641 --> 00:03:46,184
You couldn't find a bone.

56
00:03:46,976 --> 00:03:49,145
Turning people into stew. Sick fucks.

57
00:03:49,771 --> 00:03:50,730
Who told you that?

58
00:03:51,606 --> 00:03:52,982
I visited Seung-deok in prison.

59
00:03:53,066 --> 00:03:55,193
How does that punk know this
when he's locked up?

60
00:03:55,276 --> 00:03:57,862
Prison is the best source
for information like this.

61
00:03:59,280 --> 00:04:00,907
You guys all right back there?

62
00:04:01,449 --> 00:04:02,992
- Yes, sir.
- Yes. We're all right, sir.

63
00:04:03,076 --> 00:04:05,536
Seeing all that couldn't have been easy.

64
00:04:07,789 --> 00:04:11,626
By the way, what will happen
when they open the casino?

65
00:04:11,709 --> 00:04:12,710
What will happen?

66
00:04:13,836 --> 00:04:15,588
Kim Myeong-gil will make lots of money.

67
00:04:15,672 --> 00:04:17,006
- Oh.
- Gun-woo.

68
00:04:17,507 --> 00:04:18,341
Sir.

69
00:04:18,424 --> 00:04:22,428
Gambling and drug addicts
take out a lot of private loans.

70
00:04:22,512 --> 00:04:25,556
Kim Myeong-gil connects the casino
with moneylending.

71
00:04:26,057 --> 00:04:30,061
The more people visit his casino,
the more people will take out loans.

72
00:04:30,561 --> 00:04:32,981
He'll just rake in easy money day by day.

73
00:04:33,940 --> 00:04:35,984
But I thought
only foreigners could go to casinos.

74
00:04:36,651 --> 00:04:38,820
Do you think
Kim Myeong-gil cares about the law?

75
00:04:38,903 --> 00:04:41,489
He'll let all the big spenders in
through the back door.

76
00:04:41,572 --> 00:04:44,242
They're not going to make any money
operating legally.

77
00:04:44,742 --> 00:04:47,370
Once he's made enough money,

78
00:04:47,453 --> 00:04:49,289
Kim Myeong-gil will buy a building
with a loan.

79
00:04:49,372 --> 00:04:53,668
Then he'll use that building as collateral
for another loan to buy a bigger building.

80
00:04:53,751 --> 00:04:54,627
Man.

81
00:04:55,128 --> 00:04:56,713
That asshole's a real piece of work.

82
00:04:56,796 --> 00:05:00,258
He'll go even harder running the casino
to pay back that loan.

83
00:05:00,341 --> 00:05:03,177
And Smile Capital will squeeze
even more people dry.

84
00:05:03,261 --> 00:05:06,055
It'll be the opening
of Kim Myeong-gil's personal kingdom.

85
00:05:18,192 --> 00:05:22,739
The money Myeong-gil stole from me
back then was worth over 20 billion won

86
00:05:22,822 --> 00:05:23,781
at the time.

87
00:05:23,865 --> 00:05:25,408
Once we get it back,

88
00:05:25,491 --> 00:05:27,869
how would you feel
about taking a trip around the world

89
00:05:27,952 --> 00:05:29,829
with Gun-woo and Woo-jin, huh?

90
00:05:30,955 --> 00:05:33,082
We have enough money as it is.

91
00:05:35,084 --> 00:05:36,002
That's true.

92
00:05:36,919 --> 00:05:38,755
And we can't travel because of COVID

93
00:05:40,798 --> 00:05:41,632
True.

94
00:05:43,343 --> 00:05:44,635
Why don't we go to Rome together?

95
00:05:47,555 --> 00:05:48,556
Why Rome?

96
00:05:48,639 --> 00:05:52,101
When I was 20,
I watched a film called Roman Holiday.

97
00:05:53,019 --> 00:05:56,105
Back then, I vowed to go one day
when I made a lot of money,

98
00:05:56,189 --> 00:05:57,857
but I haven't had the chance yet.

99
00:05:58,441 --> 00:06:02,111
I thought it might be nice
to go with you all,

100
00:06:02,195 --> 00:06:03,446
the three of you, you know?

101
00:06:07,492 --> 00:06:09,827
If we go,
I'll buy you guys anything you want.

102
00:06:10,912 --> 00:06:14,040
Grandpa, Italy is way too expensive.

103
00:06:14,123 --> 00:06:15,541
It's the land of luxury.

104
00:06:16,125 --> 00:06:18,711
Look, kid, I'm Choi Tae-ho, all right?

105
00:06:19,796 --> 00:06:21,672
I'll show you how to really spend money.

106
00:06:23,716 --> 00:06:26,803
Grandpa, that's called "flexing," okay?

107
00:06:27,970 --> 00:06:31,474
Yeah, well, I'll show you flexing.
I'll do some big flexing.

108
00:06:32,558 --> 00:06:35,269
Not big flexing. You just say "flex."

109
00:06:38,064 --> 00:06:38,940
Flex.

110
00:06:44,404 --> 00:06:48,282
So when this is over,
we'll all go together, okay?

111
00:07:04,757 --> 00:07:05,591
Hello, sir.

112
00:07:06,884 --> 00:07:08,302
That sounds good, sir.

113
00:07:09,345 --> 00:07:10,179
Yes.

114
00:07:11,264 --> 00:07:14,392
Hm. Mr. Choi invited us
for drinks at his place.

115
00:07:16,519 --> 00:07:18,271
I guess he's in a pretty good mood.

116
00:07:19,605 --> 00:07:20,940
Hey, you guys drink?

117
00:07:21,941 --> 00:07:22,900
You know it!

118
00:08:17,914 --> 00:08:19,081
Can we speed it up a little?

119
00:08:19,165 --> 00:08:21,375
There's double
and quadruple-speed playback. Which one?

120
00:08:21,459 --> 00:08:23,252
- Let's make it double.
- Got it.

121
00:08:30,092 --> 00:08:32,053
If I was Kim Myeong-gil,

122
00:08:32,136 --> 00:08:35,681
I would've thought to move the hard drive
to a safer location by now,

123
00:08:35,765 --> 00:08:38,434
just in case
Im Jang-do revealed my weaknesses.

124
00:08:39,227 --> 00:08:41,771
Do you think he can afford that?

125
00:08:42,522 --> 00:08:43,981
We've boxed him into a corner.

126
00:08:44,982 --> 00:08:48,319
He has no one left to help him now
except for that Mr. Jung guy.

127
00:08:49,362 --> 00:08:50,238
Besides,

128
00:08:51,155 --> 00:08:54,116
I don't think that
Kim Myeong-gil would trust just anyone.

129
00:08:55,368 --> 00:08:57,036
He doesn't have to move it far.

130
00:08:57,119 --> 00:08:59,413
He could hide it in the trunk of a car,
and we wouldn't find it.

131
00:08:59,497 --> 00:09:01,541
- Hm.
- Kim Myeong-gil knows that.

132
00:09:02,250 --> 00:09:03,292
You're right.

133
00:09:03,918 --> 00:09:05,878
The tides would turn in our favor

134
00:09:05,962 --> 00:09:08,798
if we manage to recruit an enemy of his
over to our side.

135
00:09:11,551 --> 00:09:13,970
But to do that, we need the hard drive.

136
00:09:14,053 --> 00:09:17,598
It should contain everything
about Myeong-gil's blackmail victims.

137
00:09:18,099 --> 00:09:20,643
Those people share our motivations.

138
00:09:21,394 --> 00:09:24,146
And there will be many powerful people,

139
00:09:24,230 --> 00:09:26,399
like the heir of the Iil Group
mixed in with the bunch.

140
00:09:29,110 --> 00:09:31,821
The longer this fight drags on,
the less likely we'll come out on top.

141
00:09:32,488 --> 00:09:35,741
I'm sure Myeong-gil has made
a vast network of connections by now.

142
00:09:36,367 --> 00:09:39,245
Every cop, prosecutor, and politician
that could be bought

143
00:09:39,328 --> 00:09:42,039
is probably in his pocket by now.

144
00:09:42,665 --> 00:09:45,668
We can't ever let our guard down,
or else we're finished.

145
00:09:46,544 --> 00:09:47,545
Yeah.

146
00:09:48,129 --> 00:09:51,173
But it's true we've taken down
three of his thugs, right?

147
00:09:53,593 --> 00:09:56,262
It makes sense that we get anxious
when looking at the big picture,

148
00:09:56,887 --> 00:09:59,599
but the way I see it,
I think we're doing pretty well.

149
00:09:59,682 --> 00:10:01,225
I mean, no one's gotten hurt so far.

150
00:10:01,892 --> 00:10:02,727
That's true.

151
00:10:03,561 --> 00:10:05,271
Let's take things one at a time.

152
00:10:05,354 --> 00:10:08,274
We can take Kim Myeong-gil down
and then his company.

153
00:10:08,899 --> 00:10:12,153
Besides, now that Im Jang-do
and Kim Jun-min's out of the picture,

154
00:10:12,236 --> 00:10:14,530
Kim Myeong-gil must be feeling
the noose tighten.

155
00:10:17,158 --> 00:10:18,951
I guess she does have a point.

156
00:10:20,828 --> 00:10:22,163
Mm…

157
00:10:25,041 --> 00:10:26,792
Ah, yes, um,

158
00:10:26,876 --> 00:10:28,461
Mr. Choi, sirs.

159
00:10:31,547 --> 00:10:36,135
I would like to propose a toast
for everyone's safety and our shared goal.

160
00:10:37,470 --> 00:10:40,014
When I say, "Find that hard drive
we will do,"

161
00:10:40,097 --> 00:10:42,266
then you say,
"Kim Myeong-gil, you are through."

162
00:10:43,768 --> 00:10:45,686
I'd appreciate it if you said it loud.

163
00:10:45,770 --> 00:10:47,355
Let's get started. Raise your glasses.

164
00:10:49,398 --> 00:10:51,108
Find that hard drive, yes we do.

165
00:10:51,192 --> 00:10:53,694
- Kim Myeong-gil.
- You are through!

166
00:11:44,662 --> 00:11:46,956
I'm on my way over
to Joongang Police Station.

167
00:11:47,039 --> 00:11:49,250
Those assholes moved
from Dongpa-gu to Joongang-gu.

168
00:11:50,084 --> 00:11:51,419
Can you find them by 3:00?

169
00:11:52,837 --> 00:11:55,381
I'll find them soon
if they stopped in Joongang-gu,

170
00:11:55,464 --> 00:11:58,551
but if they crossed over,
I'll have to keep looking, I guess.

171
00:12:00,344 --> 00:12:01,512
Please, bro.

172
00:12:01,595 --> 00:12:03,097
Don't worry about it.

173
00:12:03,180 --> 00:12:05,725
We'll do what the bastard wants for now.

174
00:12:06,767 --> 00:12:09,979
Once we make it past this,
I'll think of a way to fuck this guy up.

175
00:12:11,021 --> 00:12:12,231
Thank you. Seriously.

176
00:12:12,314 --> 00:12:13,607
Min-beom,

177
00:12:13,691 --> 00:12:16,944
you think I'd just let some asshole
mess with my family like this?

178
00:12:17,570 --> 00:12:18,404
It'll be fine.

179
00:12:18,487 --> 00:12:19,447
Okay?

180
00:12:19,530 --> 00:12:20,948
You're all I have right now.

181
00:12:22,074 --> 00:12:23,993
Don't drink too much, okay?

182
00:12:24,910 --> 00:12:25,786
Mm.

183
00:12:34,086 --> 00:12:35,838
Jeez.

184
00:12:46,515 --> 00:12:49,226
Why did he drink so much
if he's such a lightweight?

185
00:12:51,187 --> 00:12:53,355
I guess
he was in a pretty good mood today.

186
00:12:53,439 --> 00:12:54,815
I'm going to bed. What about you?

187
00:12:54,899 --> 00:12:56,400
I'm going to head back downstairs.

188
00:12:56,484 --> 00:12:58,235
- Aren't you tired?
- Not really.

189
00:13:01,947 --> 00:13:02,782
Good work today.

190
00:13:02,865 --> 00:13:03,824
Yeah.

191
00:13:10,122 --> 00:13:10,956
Gun-woo.

192
00:13:12,374 --> 00:13:13,417
Gun-woo?

193
00:13:15,336 --> 00:13:16,253
You're not asleep?

194
00:13:17,379 --> 00:13:18,923
No, why are you awake?

195
00:13:19,006 --> 00:13:21,008
Oh, everyone is downstairs having a drink.

196
00:13:21,091 --> 00:13:22,343
You're drinking too?

197
00:13:22,426 --> 00:13:23,928
Mm-mm. Not me.

198
00:13:24,011 --> 00:13:24,887
Good.

199
00:13:26,680 --> 00:13:28,933
I guess I'll make hangover soup
in the morning.

200
00:13:29,016 --> 00:13:30,935
Great. Get some sleep.
I'll close the door.

201
00:13:31,018 --> 00:13:32,561
Okay, sleep tight.

202
00:13:32,645 --> 00:13:33,813
Good night, Mom.

203
00:13:36,106 --> 00:13:39,068
God, it's been so long
since we drank together.

204
00:13:40,986 --> 00:13:41,946
Mm.

205
00:13:58,337 --> 00:13:59,171
Is it a woman?

206
00:13:59,755 --> 00:14:02,925
Who would call you this late at night?

207
00:14:07,221 --> 00:14:08,138
Tell me.

208
00:14:10,766 --> 00:14:11,600
Hey…

209
00:14:14,478 --> 00:14:15,813
I'm going to be a dad.

210
00:14:17,523 --> 00:14:18,524
When?

211
00:14:19,108 --> 00:14:21,902
In two months. It's a girl.

212
00:14:23,571 --> 00:14:25,698
We've been together for three years now.

213
00:14:26,657 --> 00:14:30,077
Hey, man, if you had family,
you should've told me, you idiot.

214
00:14:30,160 --> 00:14:32,329
Then you would've told me not to come.

215
00:14:36,584 --> 00:14:38,502
Go home now. I'll wrap things up here.

216
00:14:38,586 --> 00:14:40,963
It's been so long
since we had a drink together.

217
00:14:41,046 --> 00:14:42,131
I want to stay.

218
00:14:42,214 --> 00:14:43,632
I said go home.

219
00:14:44,550 --> 00:14:46,093
Oh, don't be mad.

220
00:14:49,054 --> 00:14:49,889
Here.

221
00:14:50,931 --> 00:14:51,807
No, I'm good.

222
00:14:52,850 --> 00:14:55,352
It's not for you. Get your wife some meat.

223
00:14:55,436 --> 00:14:57,980
She needs iron right now. Come on.

224
00:15:00,608 --> 00:15:01,817
It's too much.

225
00:15:05,029 --> 00:15:06,113
Aren't you coming downstairs?

226
00:15:06,780 --> 00:15:07,781
Yeah, I'm coming.

227
00:15:07,865 --> 00:15:09,491
- I'll go on ahead.
- Sure.

228
00:15:11,994 --> 00:15:13,078
Call a cab.

229
00:15:13,162 --> 00:15:15,414
I'll have another smoke
until it gets here.

230
00:15:17,374 --> 00:15:18,208
Hey.

231
00:15:21,795 --> 00:15:22,630
Thank you.

232
00:15:24,048 --> 00:15:25,341
Don't make it weird.

233
00:15:27,718 --> 00:15:30,638
You're the best, you know?

234
00:15:31,138 --> 00:15:33,390
I'm going to get some hanwoo
on my way back.

235
00:15:37,311 --> 00:15:38,646
Oh.

236
00:15:38,729 --> 00:15:40,731
Hyeon-ju says she's going to bed early.

237
00:15:40,814 --> 00:15:41,649
Hm.

238
00:15:44,109 --> 00:15:45,027
Are you all right?

239
00:15:45,736 --> 00:15:46,570
Yes.

240
00:15:53,827 --> 00:15:55,496
You seem really worried right now, sir.

241
00:15:56,163 --> 00:15:59,291
I'm the one who taught Myeong-gil.
He's my responsibility.

242
00:16:00,250 --> 00:16:03,837
But when my body… broke down,

243
00:16:05,839 --> 00:16:07,091
I couldn't fight him.

244
00:16:09,176 --> 00:16:10,302
The only thing

245
00:16:11,887 --> 00:16:14,473
that I could manage
was taking care of Hyeon-ju.

246
00:17:25,669 --> 00:17:26,795
Who are you?

247
00:17:27,713 --> 00:17:28,589
Oh, I--

248
00:17:29,631 --> 00:17:30,507
I'm a friend

249
00:17:32,259 --> 00:17:33,635
of your father's.

250
00:17:38,682 --> 00:17:41,351
Oh no. Don't cry. Don't cry.

251
00:17:43,729 --> 00:17:44,688
Hey.

252
00:17:46,982 --> 00:17:47,900
Papa!

253
00:17:53,280 --> 00:17:56,617
CONDOLENCES

254
00:17:58,285 --> 00:17:59,411
Sorry for your loss.

255
00:18:00,871 --> 00:18:02,831
Get the best condolence flowers you can,

256
00:18:02,915 --> 00:18:05,042
then fill up the room with them.

257
00:18:05,125 --> 00:18:05,959
Yes, sir.

258
00:18:06,043 --> 00:18:07,377
Have ten men guard the place

259
00:18:07,461 --> 00:18:09,546
until they're done moving the coffin
to the grave site.

260
00:18:10,255 --> 00:18:12,049
- Should we arm them?
- Uh, no.

261
00:18:12,549 --> 00:18:14,843
It's for the child.
She's doing the wake alone.

262
00:18:14,927 --> 00:18:16,178
And let's get her some food.

263
00:18:16,261 --> 00:18:17,221
Yes, sir.

264
00:18:18,597 --> 00:18:21,391
Sir, I think you left your scarf inside.

265
00:18:21,475 --> 00:18:22,768
Oh, don't worry about it.

266
00:18:25,395 --> 00:18:27,397
Why on earth did he kill himself?

267
00:18:28,023 --> 00:18:30,984
He delivered papers in the morning,
made parts at a factory,

268
00:18:31,068 --> 00:18:32,778
and worked as a chauffeur at night.

269
00:18:32,861 --> 00:18:35,155
He got just three hours of sleep every day

270
00:18:35,239 --> 00:18:37,991
for two years working graveyard shifts
to save his daughter.

271
00:18:38,075 --> 00:18:40,828
Then his child gets better,
and he kills himself?

272
00:18:41,703 --> 00:18:42,788
I just don't get it.

273
00:18:43,664 --> 00:18:45,666
I told him
that I didn't need any interest.

274
00:18:45,749 --> 00:18:47,876
He just had to pay back the principal,

275
00:18:47,960 --> 00:18:50,921
and I'd give him an extension
if he ever needed more time.

276
00:18:58,428 --> 00:19:00,347
Um, I'll look into it.

277
00:19:00,931 --> 00:19:02,307
I just don't understand.

278
00:19:10,524 --> 00:19:11,400
Here.

279
00:19:15,946 --> 00:19:16,864
Third floor.

280
00:19:25,914 --> 00:19:26,874
Excuse me.

281
00:19:29,126 --> 00:19:29,960
Jesus.

282
00:19:30,544 --> 00:19:33,505
Are you, by chance, on your way
to Mr. Cha Sang-ho's funeral?

283
00:19:35,174 --> 00:19:36,008
Yes.

284
00:19:39,678 --> 00:19:43,557
Two years ago, when I got surgery
and couldn't lift things,

285
00:19:44,057 --> 00:19:48,520
Hyeon-ju's dad would take out the trash
for me for three months.

286
00:19:49,855 --> 00:19:54,610
God, he was the nicest,
hardest-working person around.

287
00:19:55,944 --> 00:19:57,738
I felt so bad for Hyeon-ju.

288
00:19:58,238 --> 00:20:01,450
That poor little thing sick
without a mother around.

289
00:20:02,034 --> 00:20:04,953
I used to feed her
and fill up their fridge,

290
00:20:05,454 --> 00:20:07,206
so they didn't run out things to eat.

291
00:20:07,289 --> 00:20:11,168
Why would he kill himself
now that Hyeon-ju has gotten better?

292
00:20:11,251 --> 00:20:14,421
It's because of the loan shark bastards!

293
00:20:15,130 --> 00:20:17,257
They used to come over
whenever they pleased,

294
00:20:18,258 --> 00:20:22,054
grabbing him by the neck
and beating him. God--

295
00:20:22,137 --> 00:20:23,096
What did they look like?

296
00:20:24,056 --> 00:20:27,893
Uh, well,
one was almost the size of a brown bear.

297
00:20:28,393 --> 00:20:31,104
The other one was tall, incredibly tall.

298
00:20:34,107 --> 00:20:35,359
One month later,

299
00:20:35,984 --> 00:20:39,196
another person I had lent money to
killed themselves.

300
00:20:40,072 --> 00:20:42,824
It was also someone
I had given an interest-free loan

301
00:20:42,908 --> 00:20:44,743
because of a sick family member.

302
00:20:46,161 --> 00:20:48,330
I'm going home too soon.

303
00:20:50,165 --> 00:20:51,291
Watch the stairs.

304
00:20:55,545 --> 00:20:56,880
Ah, my brother.

305
00:21:03,220 --> 00:21:04,096
I'll go now.

306
00:21:05,555 --> 00:21:07,224
- Get home safe.
- Okay.

307
00:21:09,059 --> 00:21:10,060
Good night.

308
00:21:16,358 --> 00:21:18,026
Yang-jung found out later

309
00:21:18,777 --> 00:21:21,113
that the people
that I had given those loans

310
00:21:21,196 --> 00:21:23,365
for their family's medical expenses

311
00:21:25,367 --> 00:21:27,411
had been visited by Myeong-gil.

312
00:21:27,494 --> 00:21:29,871
He was going around taking several million

313
00:21:29,955 --> 00:21:31,915
in loan extension fees from them
every month,

314
00:21:33,375 --> 00:21:35,711
telling them
that he was following my orders.

315
00:21:37,004 --> 00:21:40,215
My mom fell for the same trick.

316
00:21:41,842 --> 00:21:44,177
He hid a clause in the fine print
within the contract.

317
00:21:47,139 --> 00:21:48,098
Oh.

318
00:21:49,850 --> 00:21:51,143
I'm so sorry.

319
00:21:53,812 --> 00:21:55,856
A lot of people got hurt because of me.

320
00:21:56,648 --> 00:21:57,649
That's not true.

321
00:21:58,650 --> 00:22:01,320
You don't need to feel sorry
for what happened to us, Mr. Choi.

322
00:22:02,029 --> 00:22:05,365
I think you have a strong sense
of responsibility,

323
00:22:05,449 --> 00:22:07,284
which is why you feel so much guilt.

324
00:22:08,035 --> 00:22:10,746
Those who are truly shameless
feel no guilt whatsoever.

325
00:22:11,455 --> 00:22:15,000
They always blame others
and prey on people weaker than them.

326
00:22:17,294 --> 00:22:19,755
But I think the only reason
why we're all gathered here today

327
00:22:19,838 --> 00:22:22,215
is because of the goodwill you've spread
throughout the years.

328
00:22:22,799 --> 00:22:27,429
I don't think Hyeon-ju knows
that you bought the orphanage for her,

329
00:22:28,597 --> 00:22:30,223
but I'm sure
she will always believe in you

330
00:22:30,307 --> 00:22:31,433
with all her heart.

331
00:22:32,017 --> 00:22:32,851
We'll work together

332
00:22:32,934 --> 00:22:35,103
and bring Kim Myeong-gil down
no matter what.

333
00:22:35,687 --> 00:22:37,314
So please stop blaming yourself,

334
00:22:39,191 --> 00:22:41,276
and please take care of your health, sir.

335
00:22:55,624 --> 00:22:59,544
When we're done, I'll set you up
with your own private boxing gym.

336
00:23:00,045 --> 00:23:01,755
That should help you focus
on your training

337
00:23:01,838 --> 00:23:04,049
until you eventually become a champion.

338
00:23:04,674 --> 00:23:08,845
And I'll build a nice big café
for your mom on the ground floor.

339
00:23:10,013 --> 00:23:12,057
No rent until the day I die.

340
00:23:13,517 --> 00:23:14,351
Wow.

341
00:23:17,813 --> 00:23:20,273
What, you don't know what to say
all of a sudden?

342
00:23:20,357 --> 00:23:21,191
No.

343
00:23:23,360 --> 00:23:24,736
A thank you would do.

344
00:23:26,154 --> 00:23:26,988
Oh.

345
00:23:28,115 --> 00:23:29,533
Thank you so much, Mr. Choi.

346
00:23:29,616 --> 00:23:30,534
No.

347
00:23:32,619 --> 00:23:34,621
I'm the one that should be thanking you.

348
00:23:36,289 --> 00:23:38,458
You're teaching me
what youth is all about.

349
00:23:40,961 --> 00:23:41,878
This is…

350
00:23:43,964 --> 00:23:44,798
flex!

351
00:23:46,466 --> 00:23:47,467
Right?

352
00:23:47,551 --> 00:23:48,718
Yes.

353
00:23:53,682 --> 00:23:55,559
- Let's take a look over there.
- Here?

354
00:23:55,642 --> 00:23:57,394
- No, no. Next to it.
- Oh, all right.

355
00:24:14,119 --> 00:24:16,288
- How about up there? That part.
- Oh, all right.

356
00:24:30,969 --> 00:24:32,304
- All right. Thank you.
- Okay.

357
00:24:32,387 --> 00:24:33,472
Good job.

358
00:24:47,319 --> 00:24:48,487
GANG-YONG

359
00:24:50,572 --> 00:24:52,824
- Yes.
- Onyu-ro 88.

360
00:24:53,909 --> 00:24:54,784
Will that do?

361
00:24:55,827 --> 00:24:57,078
Thank you very much.

362
00:25:08,298 --> 00:25:10,008
- Let's go.
- Yes, sir!

363
00:26:24,416 --> 00:26:25,417
Look.

364
00:26:29,963 --> 00:26:31,631
President Choi is on crutches.

365
00:26:45,228 --> 00:26:46,104
Hm.

366
00:26:46,938 --> 00:26:48,273
They tortured him.

367
00:26:50,609 --> 00:26:51,776
Did he rat us out?

368
00:26:52,444 --> 00:26:53,737
I'm not sure, sir.

369
00:26:54,738 --> 00:26:55,655
Hm.

370
00:26:56,615 --> 00:26:58,867
It's much safer for us to assume he did.

371
00:26:59,367 --> 00:27:01,870
Let's get President Choi.

372
00:27:04,289 --> 00:27:05,332
Then Jang-do.

373
00:27:06,416 --> 00:27:07,542
Yes, sir.

374
00:27:12,130 --> 00:27:13,214
Um, sir.

375
00:27:18,887 --> 00:27:21,056
LEE DU-YEONG

376
00:27:29,606 --> 00:27:31,733
Make sure you don't kill the guy.

377
00:27:32,609 --> 00:27:34,027
I need information.

378
00:27:34,110 --> 00:27:34,944
Yes, sir.

379
00:27:35,612 --> 00:27:37,906
- And take off that thing.
- Oh.

380
00:27:40,075 --> 00:27:40,950
Mm.

381
00:28:07,727 --> 00:28:08,895
Honey.

382
00:28:10,230 --> 00:28:11,940
Someone's at the door.

383
00:28:28,081 --> 00:28:29,249
Who is it?

384
00:28:29,332 --> 00:28:30,625
Uh, I'm from downstairs.

385
00:28:30,709 --> 00:28:33,461
I'm here because there's water leaking
from our ceiling.

386
00:28:33,962 --> 00:28:36,464
Would you mind
if I came in to check your bathroom?

387
00:28:40,260 --> 00:28:41,720
I promise this won't take long.

388
00:28:41,803 --> 00:28:43,555
It's just
that our house is flooded right now.

389
00:28:44,681 --> 00:28:47,142
Our kids haven't gotten any sleep
because of this.

390
00:28:48,727 --> 00:28:50,311
I would really appreciate it.

391
00:28:53,565 --> 00:28:54,482
Right now?

392
00:28:54,566 --> 00:28:56,109
Yes, it won't take long.

393
00:28:56,943 --> 00:28:58,445
I'll just check your bathroom.

394
00:29:12,125 --> 00:29:14,586
- Honey?
- Hm?

395
00:29:17,172 --> 00:29:19,841
- Who is it?
- He says water is leaking downstairs.

396
00:29:23,428 --> 00:29:24,512
- Move over, honey.
- Huh?

397
00:29:24,596 --> 00:29:25,430
Move over.

398
00:29:30,560 --> 00:29:31,603
Shh.

399
00:29:32,520 --> 00:29:33,396
Huh?

400
00:29:39,194 --> 00:29:40,445
- Just a second.
- Okay.

401
00:29:55,251 --> 00:29:59,047
Listen to me.
Call the cops now and report a burglary.

402
00:29:59,130 --> 00:30:02,300
- Why?
- I'll explain later.

403
00:30:03,176 --> 00:30:04,177
You trust me, right?

404
00:30:05,094 --> 00:30:05,929
Yes.

405
00:30:06,012 --> 00:30:07,263
And also,

406
00:30:07,889 --> 00:30:09,015
no matter what,

407
00:30:10,558 --> 00:30:12,268
do not open the door, you hear me?

408
00:30:12,352 --> 00:30:13,978
Okay.

409
00:30:15,563 --> 00:30:16,523
Mm-hm.

410
00:30:16,606 --> 00:30:18,775
It's all right, honey.

411
00:30:18,858 --> 00:30:20,985
Nothing's going to happen. It's all right.

412
00:30:25,281 --> 00:30:26,199
Okay.

413
00:30:51,182 --> 00:30:52,392
Dongjak-gu, Samjin-dong.

414
00:31:06,698 --> 00:31:08,283
Please, please!

415
00:31:08,366 --> 00:31:10,159
Hurry. My husband's in danger.

416
00:31:21,504 --> 00:31:24,048
- Come on, come on. Let's go.
- Get in there. Go.

417
00:31:24,132 --> 00:31:25,842
Where is he?

418
00:31:31,306 --> 00:31:33,933
Whoa! Shit.

419
00:31:34,017 --> 00:31:36,185
Go, go, go! Go!

420
00:33:15,576 --> 00:33:16,536
Hm.

421
00:33:21,708 --> 00:33:23,626
Tell me where to find Hwang Yang-jung,

422
00:33:25,128 --> 00:33:26,671
and I'll let your girl live.

423
00:33:31,342 --> 00:33:32,760
I always keep my promises

424
00:33:34,012 --> 00:33:35,096
with no exceptions.

425
00:33:41,686 --> 00:33:42,687
Trust me.

426
00:34:13,301 --> 00:34:15,428
- Did you sleep well, Mr. Choi?
- I did.

427
00:34:16,596 --> 00:34:17,722
Did you sleep well?

428
00:34:17,805 --> 00:34:19,557
- Like a baby.
- Me too.

429
00:34:22,060 --> 00:34:23,436
Hey, sit down.

430
00:34:26,314 --> 00:34:28,274
Hey, so this is a first for us.

431
00:34:28,900 --> 00:34:30,985
Yes, we should do this more.

432
00:34:32,361 --> 00:34:34,197
Dude, get up now. Hm.

433
00:34:34,280 --> 00:34:35,239
Let's eat.

434
00:34:38,367 --> 00:34:40,787
- Oh, wow. Thank you.
- Oh, of course.

435
00:34:40,870 --> 00:34:43,206
- Mm. Yeah.
- Here.

436
00:34:43,289 --> 00:34:45,208
- He's not coming?
- He won't get up.

437
00:34:45,291 --> 00:34:47,668
God, you should've told him to eat
and then sleep.

438
00:34:47,752 --> 00:34:49,629
He got his fill last night, didn't he?

439
00:34:49,712 --> 00:34:50,922
Yes.

440
00:34:51,005 --> 00:34:53,132
All that big talk
about being a good drinker.

441
00:34:54,717 --> 00:34:56,302
- Then let's eat.
- Thank you.

442
00:34:56,385 --> 00:34:58,471
- Thank you for this meal.
- Please enjoy.

443
00:35:05,812 --> 00:35:06,854
Whoa!

444
00:35:07,897 --> 00:35:11,067
- Mm. Um, Gun-woo.
- Yes, sir?

445
00:35:11,150 --> 00:35:13,361
When are you taking your mother
to the orphanage?

446
00:35:14,153 --> 00:35:16,531
I can do it.
Let me borrow your car, Grandpa.

447
00:35:16,614 --> 00:35:18,449
It's been outside for a while.

448
00:35:18,533 --> 00:35:20,076
Someone might've seen it, so be careful.

449
00:35:20,159 --> 00:35:21,619
- I'll be okay.
- All right.

450
00:35:21,702 --> 00:35:22,870
Do you wanna go after we eat?

451
00:35:22,954 --> 00:35:24,956
This time of day,
we should make it there in an hour.

452
00:35:26,624 --> 00:35:27,542
Mom, that work for you?

453
00:35:27,625 --> 00:35:29,252
Uh, to be honest,

454
00:35:29,752 --> 00:35:32,213
I think I… I would feel a lot better

455
00:35:32,296 --> 00:35:34,715
if I just stayed here
and kept preparing meals for everyone.

456
00:35:37,552 --> 00:35:38,469
Mrs. Yoon.

457
00:35:40,304 --> 00:35:42,348
Uh, I don't mean to impose,

458
00:35:43,099 --> 00:35:45,476
but would you mind helping out
at our orphanage?

459
00:35:47,395 --> 00:35:50,481
It's just that
your cooking skills are really impressive…

460
00:35:50,565 --> 00:35:52,316
I think the children would love it.

461
00:35:54,569 --> 00:35:57,029
Mrs. Yoon, this food is just amazing.

462
00:36:01,242 --> 00:36:03,244
Mom, I also think
that would be for the best.

463
00:36:07,999 --> 00:36:11,961
- Well, okay if it helps you in any way.
- That's great. Thank you so much.

464
00:36:13,337 --> 00:36:14,172
Yes.

465
00:36:26,893 --> 00:36:30,688
So you're not going to be skipping meals,
you promise?

466
00:36:31,772 --> 00:36:32,607
Mm-hm.

467
00:36:40,281 --> 00:36:41,782
Please stay safe, sweetie.

468
00:36:43,784 --> 00:36:44,619
Mm-hm.

469
00:36:50,416 --> 00:36:51,584
Don't worry so much, okay?

470
00:36:52,168 --> 00:36:53,002
Mm.

471
00:36:54,962 --> 00:36:56,672
I won't. I believe in my son.

472
00:37:18,236 --> 00:37:21,030
HWANGSUSA

473
00:37:30,039 --> 00:37:31,916
SECURITY DISABLED

474
00:37:36,003 --> 00:37:36,879
Min-dong.

475
00:38:28,180 --> 00:38:29,348
How did you find me?

476
00:38:30,558 --> 00:38:31,475
Well,

477
00:38:32,685 --> 00:38:34,520
Lee Du-yeong told me.

478
00:38:37,398 --> 00:38:39,275
Did you do something to his girl?

479
00:38:39,900 --> 00:38:40,818
Whoa, whoa.

480
00:38:43,612 --> 00:38:44,655
You kill them?

481
00:43:26,937 --> 00:43:27,771
Let's go.

482
00:43:30,816 --> 00:43:31,942
Come on. Go.

483
00:43:50,544 --> 00:43:51,879
Mr. Choi!

484
00:43:52,463 --> 00:43:54,131
Kim Myeong-gil's thugs are outside.

485
00:43:54,214 --> 00:43:56,175
What are you talking about?

486
00:44:04,224 --> 00:44:06,518
Let's go to the basement.
There's a gun down there.

487
00:44:18,781 --> 00:44:20,824
I'll stay behind.
Hurry up and go get the gun.

488
00:44:20,908 --> 00:44:22,326
- Go!
- No, Woo-jin!

489
00:44:22,951 --> 00:44:25,162
- Damn it!
- Woo-jin, get out of there.

490
00:44:25,245 --> 00:44:26,872
Woo-jin!

491
00:44:30,584 --> 00:44:31,585
Get in there.

492
00:44:33,962 --> 00:44:35,130
No!

493
00:44:35,714 --> 00:44:37,591
Go fuck him up!

494
00:44:37,675 --> 00:44:39,009
Woo-jin!

495
00:44:41,178 --> 00:44:42,179
Go, go, go!

496
00:44:53,607 --> 00:44:55,109
You're dead, motherfucker!

497
00:45:04,451 --> 00:45:07,746
Let's get him.

498
00:45:20,926 --> 00:45:22,052
Get in there!

499
00:45:30,018 --> 00:45:31,019
Out of the way!

500
00:47:06,865 --> 00:47:09,117
Woo-jin! Woo-jin!

501
00:47:26,510 --> 00:47:27,845
Woo-jin!

502
00:48:14,057 --> 00:48:14,892
Sir.

503
00:48:17,603 --> 00:48:19,688
- Where is he?
- This way, sir.

504
00:48:20,188 --> 00:48:21,023
Get pouring, you two.

505
00:48:21,106 --> 00:48:22,608
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

506
00:48:23,567 --> 00:48:25,068
groaning

507
00:48:28,906 --> 00:48:30,240
Blood, ugh.

508
00:48:46,715 --> 00:48:47,633
Well done.

509
00:48:55,641 --> 00:48:56,850
You are actually…

510
00:48:58,852 --> 00:49:00,354
someone I'm grateful for.

511
00:49:00,437 --> 00:49:01,813
Hey, over here.

512
00:49:04,274 --> 00:49:05,192
You see,

513
00:49:06,193 --> 00:49:07,986
you gave me a dream.

514
00:49:08,070 --> 00:49:10,113
You…

515
00:49:14,326 --> 00:49:16,495
That's why…

516
00:49:18,956 --> 00:49:20,624
…I'm going to make this painless.

517
00:49:21,500 --> 00:49:22,709
Oh, it's all right.

518
00:49:24,252 --> 00:49:27,005
It'll be over quick. It's all right.
You won't feel anything.

519
00:49:27,673 --> 00:49:29,049
Yeah, there.

520
00:49:34,054 --> 00:49:36,098
It's all right. Ah, it's all right.

521
00:50:02,332 --> 00:50:03,166
Mm.

522
00:50:19,933 --> 00:50:21,184
Gun-woo.

523
00:50:36,825 --> 00:50:38,243
- Try the back door.
- Okay.

524
00:50:51,423 --> 00:50:52,466
Woo-jin!

525
00:51:06,063 --> 00:51:06,897
No!

526
00:51:35,258 --> 00:51:36,384
Hyeon-ju!

527
00:51:37,636 --> 00:51:39,096
Jesus, Hyeon-ju!

528
00:51:44,017 --> 00:51:45,102
Just hold on.

529
00:51:47,354 --> 00:51:48,188
Grandpa.

530
00:51:51,733 --> 00:51:52,567
Grandpa.

531
00:51:53,068 --> 00:51:56,446
Grandpa! Grandpa!

532
00:51:56,530 --> 00:51:58,865
Oh God, Grandpa.

533
00:51:58,949 --> 00:52:01,284
Grandpa!

534
00:52:03,954 --> 00:52:06,414
Get up, please. You're not dead.

535
00:52:11,253 --> 00:52:14,589
Oh God! No, no! Gun-woo!

536
00:52:16,800 --> 00:52:19,052
Gun-woo, come! Gun-woo!

537
00:52:20,178 --> 00:52:22,389
Grandpa, please get up.

538
00:52:23,056 --> 00:52:26,560
Please, please help. Please, please.

539
00:52:28,770 --> 00:52:30,647
Grandpa.

540
00:52:30,730 --> 00:52:32,691
- We need to get out, Hyeon-ju.
- No!

541
00:52:32,774 --> 00:52:35,277
- We have to get out! Hurry!
- No, no. We can't! Let go!

542
00:52:35,360 --> 00:52:37,028
If you stay here, you'll die too!

543
00:52:37,529 --> 00:52:40,031
Grandpa! Grandpa!

544
00:52:40,115 --> 00:52:41,658
Let go of me!

545
00:52:59,885 --> 00:53:00,802
Scalpel.

546
00:53:03,972 --> 00:53:05,849
Suction! Some more gauze, please.

547
00:53:12,022 --> 00:53:14,191
- What's the patient's status?
- BP's 80/50!

548
00:53:14,274 --> 00:53:15,317
Starting blood transfusion!

549
00:53:15,400 --> 00:53:18,236
We're short on blood because of COVID.
We'll need to get it elsewhere.

550
00:53:18,320 --> 00:53:20,030
Get us as much as you can somehow.

551
00:53:20,113 --> 00:53:21,156
Clip!

552
00:53:29,164 --> 00:53:31,374
- Then what do we do?
- His other legal guardian--

553
00:53:31,458 --> 00:53:32,417
What is it?

554
00:53:32,500 --> 00:53:34,502
They're saying
they don't have enough blood for Woo-jin.

555
00:53:34,586 --> 00:53:36,171
- Oh, God.
- What's your blood type?

556
00:53:36,254 --> 00:53:39,049
- It's Type A.
- Come with me.

557
00:53:42,177 --> 00:53:45,180
I promise I'll save Woo-jin
no matter what, so don't worry. Okay?

558
00:53:45,263 --> 00:53:46,806
Okay.

559
00:53:59,653 --> 00:54:01,988
He's losing a lot of blood.

560
00:54:02,072 --> 00:54:04,449
Please, we need more blood now!

561
00:54:05,116 --> 00:54:06,076
We need more gauze.

562
00:54:06,701 --> 00:54:08,161
I need it now. Please hurry.

563
00:54:09,996 --> 00:54:10,997
All done.

564
00:54:11,665 --> 00:54:13,541
Is this enough to save Hong Woo-jin?

565
00:54:13,625 --> 00:54:15,585
No, I think we'll need a couple more bags.

566
00:54:15,669 --> 00:54:16,503
Oh.

567
00:54:17,003 --> 00:54:19,172
Okay, then let me
just fill up another one please.

568
00:54:19,256 --> 00:54:21,466
We've already gotten too much.
More would put you at risk.

569
00:54:21,549 --> 00:54:24,761
Oh, don't worry about it. I'm a boxer.
It'll take more than this to kill me.

570
00:54:24,844 --> 00:54:26,638
- It's fine.
- I'm sorry. I can't

571
00:54:26,721 --> 00:54:29,474
Listen to me.
I really, really have to save him. Please.

572
00:54:29,557 --> 00:54:32,519
Please just let me fill up another one.

573
00:54:32,602 --> 00:54:34,145
- Please, I'm begging you.
- I really can't.

574
00:54:34,229 --> 00:54:35,981
This won't kill me, really.

575
00:54:36,064 --> 00:54:39,985
Please,
I have to save Woo-jin.

576
00:54:40,068 --> 00:54:41,444
I have to save him.

577
00:54:41,528 --> 00:54:43,446
I really won't die.
Please, I'm begging you.

578
00:54:43,530 --> 00:54:46,324
I'm begging you. Please, please.

579
00:54:46,408 --> 00:54:47,993
I can't see due to the blood.

580
00:54:48,076 --> 00:54:49,369
- Suction!
- Applying suction.

581
00:54:49,452 --> 00:54:52,414
I can't control the bleeding.
Please prepare the Surgicel.

582
00:54:52,497 --> 00:54:54,249
Surgicel ready.

583
00:54:54,332 --> 00:54:56,751
Keep it coming.
I'll be needing more.

584
00:54:56,835 --> 00:54:59,337
Blood pressure dropping.
Please hurry. Hurry!
